Norbert Wiener, a mathematician, engineer and social philosopher,
coined the word "cybernetics" from the Greek word meaning "steersman."
He defined it as:

''The science of control and communication in the animal and the machine.''

Over time, cybernetics has been given many definitions, some of which are listed
[[here|http://www.gwu.edu/~asc/cyber_definition.html]].